Commentary: A beauty to start with! Mitchell Starc begins with a good-length delivery around off, angling away, Rohit Sharma tries to poke at it but gets beaten on the outside edge. However, there is a bit of a sound and there is an appeal for caught behind, but turned down. Australia players discuss for a bit but decides against the review. UltraEdge shows that there was an edge.
A low full toss, on middle, Rohit Sharma flicks it towards square leg where the fielder dives to his right to stop it.
Touch fuller and way outside off, angling away, Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.

This is on a hard length and on off, shaping in sharply, Rohit Sharma looks to defend, but gets hit on the pads as the ball goes towards the keeper. There is another stiffled appeal, but the finger stays down. However, Ball Tracking shows three reds and Australia gives another life to Rohit Sharma.
FOUR! Rohit Sharma and India are underway! Mitchell Starc pitches it up, on middle and leg, Rohit Sharma stays there and clips it wide of deep square leg for a boundary.
Back of a length and on middle, Rohit Sharma keeps it out to the leg side.
Cameron Green starts with a hard-length delivery, on off, Shubman Gill blocks it towards short covers.
FOUR! Shubman Gill gets off the mark in style! Cameron Green serves this full and outside off, Shubman Gill strides out a bit and drives it firmly through covers for a boundary.
On a length and on off, shaping away, Shubman Gill lets it go to the keeper.
Pitched up, on middle, nips away a bit, Shubman Gill looks to flick it away, but close the face of the bat early and gets a leading edge through covers. Two runs taken!
Pulls his length back a bit, on the fifth stump line, Shubman Gill leans on and leaves it alone.
Length again, on middle, Shubman Gill dead bats it to the off side.
Full and on middle, shaping in, Rohit Sharma knocks it towards mid on.
Full again outside off, angling away, Rohit Sharma lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper as Alex Carey collects it on two bounces.
This is on a good length and on off, angling away again, Rohit Sharma plays for the inswing and misses it completely.
Back of a length and around off, Rohit Sharma tries to cut close from his body, but misses again.
FOUR! Rohit Sharma connects this time alright! Mitchell Starc lands this short of a length and outside off, Rohit Sharma accepts the room and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Goes a bit fuller and on middle, Rohit Sharma looks to defend, but gets an outside edge as the ball goes on two bounces towards second slip. The ball is not carrying on this wicket.
This is fuller in length and around off, Shubman Gill goes for the drive on the up, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Up and over! Cameron Green serves this full again and on off, shaping away, Shubman Gill slashes hard at it, and the ball goes over the slips towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Pitched up, on off, Shubman Gill pushes it towards mid off.
Overpitched and around leg, Shubman Gill drills it towards mid on.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Cameron Green continues with his fuller length, on off, Shubman Gill takes a coupls of steps forward and times his drive perfectly through covers for another boundary.
On a length and on middle, Shubman Gill blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller one and on off, Rohit Sharma drives it towards short extra covers.
Full again and on middle, Rohit Sharma defends it towards short mid-wicket.

FOUR! Good shot! Mitchell Starc pitches this one up around off, Rohit Sharma stays there and lofts it over short covers. The timing is not that good, but it still has enough legs to go over the fence for a boundary.
This is on a good length and outside off, angling away, Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.
Nice variation! Mitchell Starc bowls the off-cutter, on off, shaping away, Rohit Sharma is early into his drive and misses it.
A yorker this time around off, Rohit Sharma jams it out towards point.
Matthew Kuhnemann starts with flatter delivery, full and on middle, Shubman Gill tucks it towards mid on for a single.
Floated, short and on middle, turning away and keeps low too, Rohit Sharma works it towards mid on.
BEATEN! This is tossed up, full and on off, turning away sharply, Rohit Sharma looks to block it, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Looped up, full and on off, turning away again, Rohit Sharma goes for the sweep, but misses it completely.
Quicker, full and on off, Rohit Sharma defends it towards short covers.

OUT! STUMPED! Matthew Kuhnemann draws first blood! Rohit Sharma tries to take on the bowler, but absolutely throws his wicket away here. Matthew Kuhnemann flights this up, on off, turning away sharply, Rohit Sharma skips down the track and goes for the big slog on the leg side, but gets beaten by the turn away and Alex Carey does the rest behind the stumps leaving Sharma halfway down the pitch. He would be disappointed with this shot as there was no need and he could not take advantage of the two lives given to him earlier. India lose their first wicket!
Howout: st Alex Carey b Matthew Kuhnemann

Commentary: This is on a hard length and on middle, Shubman Gill blocks it down the pitch.

Buzzers! This is on a good length and on middle, Shubman Gill tucks it towards short mid-wicket and sets off for the run, the fielder misses his shy at the bowler's end as Gill puts the dive in. However, the back up is not good and the ball races towards the deep extra cover fence for a boundary. Five runs added to the total!
Goes fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it towards mid off.
Full again and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it towards short covers.
On a length and around leg, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it through backward square leg for a single and gets off the mark.
Overpitched and on middle, Shubman Gill flicks it wide of mid on for a run.
Tossed up, full and on leg, Shubman Gill looks to flick, but gets a leading edge along the ground towards short covers.

OUT! TAKEN! Matthew Kuhnemann strikes again! Both the Indian openers are now back in the hut. This is floated, full and on middle inviting the batter forward, Shubman Gill obliges and tries to defend on the front foot, but the turn away takes the outside edge and Steven Smith at first slip takes a sharp catch. India two down now!
Howout: c Steven Smith b Matthew Kuhnemann

Commentary: Flighted, full and on middle, Virat Kohli dead bats it onto the pitch.
TURN AND BOUNCE! This is tossed up, full and lands around leg, turns away with extra bounce, Virat Kohli looks to flick, but misses and the ball hits Alex Carey around his shoulders.
Slower through the air, on middle, Virat Kohli knocks it past the bowler towards mid on.
A bit short, on off, keeps low too, Virat Kohli watches it through and forces it towards long off for a single and gets off the mark.
Nathan Lyon starts with a tossed up delivery, full and on middle, Virat Kohli clips it towards deep square leg for a single.

OUT! TIMBER! Nathan Lyon gets a big wicket now! A dream delivery for an off-spinner. Lyons bowls this quicker, short and outside off, grips and turns in sharply, Cheteshwar Pujara initially goes on the front foot, but then decides to go on the back foot and plays all over it as the ball goes on to rattle the stumps. Cheteshwar Pujara goes back to the hut for a low score and India are in a spot of bother.

Flighted, full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja looks to play at it, but gets an outside edge past slips towards third man where the fielder chases it down and dives to keep it inside. Three runs taken!
BEATEN! This is slower through the air, on off, straightens after hitting the deck, Virat Kohli leans on to defend, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Flatter, full and on middle, Virat Kohli drills it wide of long on where Mitchell Starc slides to his right and stops it. A single is taken.
Flighted, full and on off, turning away, Ravindra Jadeja misses as he looks to keep it out.

Tossed up, full and on leg, Virat Kohli flicks it towards mid-wicket where the fielder dives to his right and gets a hand to it, the ball rolls towards the sweeper cover fence, but Cameron Green chases it and dives to keep it inside. Three runs taken!
A bit short an on middle, Ravindra Jadeja moves back and works it towards short mid-wicket.
Floated, full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja eases it towards long on for a single.
Shorter in length and on off, Virat Kohli moves back and knocks it towards short covers.
Tossed up, full and on middle, keeps very low, Virat Kohli prods forward and keeps it out with the bottom half of the bat towards second slip.
Another one that keeps low, Virat Kohli makes room and manages to push it towards short covers.
Fuller around pads, Ravindra Jadeja flicks this to short leg for no run.
Tossed up down leg, Ravindra Jadeja works this to short fine leg.
Fuller around off, Ravindra Jadeja blocks this out with a front foot defensive stroke.

Brillant delivery from the gaffer, and Ravindra Jadeja is struck on his crease as he gets hit on the pads, floater with a bit of pace, Ravindra Jadeja jumps onto his back foot to block this but gets beaten by the pace of this. The ball hits his pads and the umpire had no doubt raising his finger to give Jadeja his marching orders. India asks for a DRS as Jadeja thinks he has edged this and the ultra-edge shows a clear spike so umpire NItin is asked to overturn his decision.

OUT! TAKEN! What is happening in Indore? India is in a situation of bother as they lose their 4th wicket without 50 on the score board. Short and wide outside off, Ravindra Jadeja looks to slap this through mid off but hits this straight in the hands of Matthew Kuhnemann at short cover who makes no mistake and accepts this with both hands.
Howout: c Matthew Kuhnemann b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Fuller around pads, Shreyas Iyer strides in front and blocks this out to the on side.
Tossed up outside off, Virat Kohli drives this to long off for a comfortable rotation of strike.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Team India is falling apart like a pack of cards here. Short and wide outside off, Shreyas Iyer looks to cut but gets a bottom edge that travels back onto the root of timber and the bails get dislodged. This track is not for the admirers of back foot stroke play as the bounce is a bit up and down here. India goes 5 down in no time and is looking shell-shocked.
On a length around pads, Srikar Bharat nudges this to mid wicket for a single.
Tossed up around middle, Virat Kohli prods forward and blocks this out.
Short in length around off, Virat Kohli defends this to slip for no run.
Touch fuller on off, Virat Kohli gets low and defends this in front. The ball kept a tad low here.
Fuller on middle, Srikar Bharat defends this right under his eyelid.
Tossed up around off, Srikar Bharat blocks this out with a front foot defensive stroke.
Length dragged back a bit, Srikar Bharat pushes this to short cover for no run.
Flighted around middle, Srikar Bharat taps this to short leg for nothing.
Fuller around middle, Srikar Bharat pushes this to long on for a single.
FOUR! Lucky escape for the champion batter. Fuller around leg, Virat Kohli clips this towards fine leg from the toe end of his bat for a boundary. This was turning and kept really low.
Fuller around off, Srikar Bharat blocks this out.
Short in length around middle, Srikar Bharat nudges this to mid wicket for a single.
FOUR! That's glorious from Virat Kohli. Fuller around middle, Virat Kohli flicks this through the mid wicket channel for a boundary. He is looking relatively comfortable on a tricky track.
Length dragged back a bit, Virat Kohli defends this off the front foot.
Tossed up around off, textbook stuff in terms of defending by Virat Kohli.
Fuller around off, Virat Kohli leans ahead and blocks this in front.
Lyon gives it a bit more air on middle, Srikar Bharat defends this to the on side.
Fuller around middle, Srikar Bharat pushes this to long on for a single.
Tossed up around off, Virat Kohli defends this right under his eyes.
Fuller outside off, Virat Kohli leans ahead and defends this in front.
Floater outside off, Virat Kohli is quick to hop onto his back foot and defend this back to the bowler.
Short in length around the pads, Virat Kohli gently taps this in front for short fine leg and runs a quick single.
Way too short on off, Virat Kohli milks this to short mid wicket.
Fuller around off, Virat Kohli pushes this to long on for a single.
Short in length from around the wicket, Srikar Bharat pushes this to wide of short cover for a quick single.
On a length angling away from stumps, Virat Kohli guides this to point and takes a single.
Fuller and quicker outside off, Srikar Bharat defends this off the front foot.

Beautifully bowled as this goes away with the arm, Srikar Bharat leans ahead to defend this but gets beaten on the outside edge. Alex Carey takes the bails off in a flash but the foot of Bharat is grounded.
Flighted on middle, Virat Kohli tucks this to short leg for no run.
Tossed up around middle, Virat Kohli flicks this to short fine leg.
Tossed up around middle, Virat Kohli flicks this towards deep square leg for a single.

Lyon gives this a bit more air and it turns off the surface, Srikar Bharat looks to play the slog sweep but misses out completely as the ball hits his pads. Aussies appeal for this and the umpire turns this one down but they opt for DRS. The ball tracker shows that the ball was missing the stumps and the on-field decision stays. Australia loses a review.
FOUR! Srikar Bharat is oozing with confidence here as this time he connects one well for a boundary. Fuller around off, Srikar Bharat slogs this towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Full and wide outside off, Srikar Bharat defends this to the off side.
Tossed up around off, Virat Kohli defends this in front.
Short in length around pads, Virat Kohli guides this to the short fine leg fielder.
Fuller around middle Virat Kohli defends this off the pads.
Length dragged back a bit around middle, Virat Kohli defends this right down the surface on the on side.
Fuller around pads, Virat Kohli defends this towards short leg.
Fuller around off, Virat Kohli gets an outside edge but safely in front of cover-point for no run.
Off-break from around the wicket drifting down leg, Srikar Bharat looks to flick but misses out. Good take from Carey behind the wicket.
Lyon gives this a bit more air and lands this full on middle, Srikar Bharat strides out to defends but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Quicker one around middle, Srikar Bharat defends this off the back foot.
Fuller around pads, Srikar Bharat pushes this towards mid wicket for a single.
Fuller outside off, Virat Kohli defends this right under his eyelid.
Tossed up around off, Virat Kohli finds the gap on the on side for a single to end the over.
Fuller outside off with a bit of pace, Virat Kohli guides this to point for no run.
Fuller around middle, Virat Kohli flicks this to short mid wicket.
Full and wide outside off, Virat Kohli blocks this out in front.
Fuller around off, Virat Kohli defends this with conviction.
Floater outside off, Virat Kohli looks to block this too but gets beaten on the outside.
Kohli uses the depth of the crease as he flicks this length delivery towards mid wicket for a single.
Floated, short and outside off, turning away, Virat Kohli gets surprised by the bounce and bunts it down towards point.
Tossed up, full and on off, Virat Kohli blocks it out towards short covers.
Flighted, full and on off, Virat Kohli leans on and keeps it out past second slip and towards point.
Shorter in length and around off, Virat Kohli moves back and punches it wide of short covers for a single.
Slower through the air, on off, turning away, Srikar Bharat prods forward and defends it as the ball falls just short of silly point.
Flatter, full and on middle, Srikar Bharat negotiates it towards silly point again.
Quicker one, bit short and on off, Virat Kohli steers it towards point.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Virat Kohli tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Floated, full and on middle, Virat Kohli defends it with the inner half towards short fine leg.

OUT! LBW! Todd Murphy gets the big fish, Virat Kohli! He flights this up around off, turning in slightly, Virat Kohli prods forward to clip it away, but close the face of the bat early and gets rapped around the pads. There is a huge appeal for LBW, and up goes the finger. However, Kohli takes the review. UltraEdge shows bat involved and Ball Tracking indicates three reds. Virat Kohli has to go back and Australian players are delighted to see the back of him. India six down now!
Flatter, full and on off, grips and turns away, Axar Patel looks to play, but misses it completely.
Darts this one full and on middle, Axar Patel drills it towards long off for a single and gets off the mark.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Axar Patel keeps it out to the off side.
Floated, full and on off, Axar Patel knocks it towards the bowler.
Lyon lands this a bit short, on middle, keeps low, Axar Patel moves back and pats it back to the bowler.
Flatter, full and on off, Axar Patel looks to defend, but gets an outside edge towards backward point.
FOUR! Nice shot! This is short and outside off, Axar Patel moves back quickly and cuts it through cover-point for a boundary.
Flighted and around off, turning further away, Axar Patel leaves it alone.
Quicker one, full and on middle, Srikar Bharat knocks it towards short covers.
SIX! BANG! Srikar Bharat goes big now! This is tossed up, full and on middle, Srikar Bharat goes down and slog-sweeps it over the deep mid-wicket fence for the first maximum of thie Test match.
Fires this one full and on the pads, Srikar Bharat clips it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Floated, full and on off, Axar Patel leans on to defend, but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball goes nowhere.
Flatter, full and on middle, Axar Patel drives it towards the bowler where Todd Murphy dives to his left to stop it.
Fires in a yorker, on middle, angling in, Axar Patel digs it out towards silly point.
A bit short and on middle, Srikar Bharat pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up and around off, fuller too, Srikar Bharat leans on to defend, but misses and gets hit high on his pads as he ball rolls towards slip.
Floated, full and on middle, Srikar Bharat blocks it out down the pitch.
Shortish and around leg, Srikar Bharat tickles it towards short fine leg.

OUT! LBW! Australia takes a great review! Nathan Lyon gets rid of Srikar Bharat now. He flights this one up, full and on middle, turning in a bit, Srikar Bharat prods forward to keep it out, but he puts his bat behind his pads and the turn in means the ball hits his front pad first. There is a huge appeal for LBW, but turned down. Steven Smith takes the review after some discussion with Nathan Lyon and Alex Carey and it turns out to be good decision as Ball Tracking indicates three reds. India seven down now!
Shortish and on leg, Ravichandran Ashwin gets hurried a bit, but keeps it down towards short leg in the end.
Back of a length and outside off, Axar Patel cuts it towards deep point for a single.
Mitchell Starc comes around the wicket and lands this short of a length, on middle, angling in, Ravichandran Ashwin blocks it down the pitch.
Mitchell Starc bangs in a bouncer, on middle and leg, Ravichandran Ashwin ducks under it.
Goes a bit fuller but down the leg side, Ravichandran Ashwin misses his flick and Alex Carey collects it behind the stumps moving to his left.
On a length and around leg, Ravichandran Ashwin helps it towards fine leg for a run and gets off the mark.
Mitchell Starc attemps the yorker, but bowls a low full toss, on off, Axar Patel mistimes his drive towards short covers. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Tossed up, full and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin steers it towards point for a single.
Fires this one full and down the leg, Axar Patel misses his flick.
Flatter and down the leg again, Axar Patel misses his flick once more as Alex Carey collects it well behind the stumps.
A bit short and on middle, Axar Patel moves back and pushes it towards long on for a run.
Gives this one some air, on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin leans on and keeps it out to the off side.
Quicker one, full and on middle, turning away, Ravichandran Ashwin dead bats it onto the pitch.
Short and around off, Axar Patel chops it towards cover-point.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Axar Patel blocks it out.
Floated, full and on leg, Axar Patel knocks it towards mid on.
Flighted, full and on middle, Axar Patel drives it back towards the bowler where Nathan Lyon gets a hand to it and makes a half stop.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Axar Patel cuts it towards deep point for a single.
Flatter and short, on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin pushes it to the right of short covers for one.

A mix-up in the middle, but no harm done! This is floated and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin uses his feet and defends it with the inner half towards square leg, Axar Patel sets off for the run, but he is sent back haflway down the pitch. However, the fielder is a bit late to get to the ball and Patel survives.
Gives this one some air, on off, keeps low, Ravichandran Ashwin knocks it to the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Matthew Kuhnemann strikes once more! Ravichandran Ashwin cannot repeat his heroics from his previous games. This is flighted nicely around middle inviting the batter forward, Ravichandran Ashwin obliges and tries to defend, but the turn away takes the slightest of outside edges and Alex Carey takes a sharp catch behind the stumps to his right. He also takes the bails off for the stumping. There is an appeal for caught behind first, but it is turned down and then Australia smartly appeals for the stumping and the square leg umpire sends it upstairs. As per protocols, the umpire have to check everything and UltraEdge shows a spike and Ashwin has to go back to the hut.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Matthew Kuhnemann

Commentary: Floated, full and on off, Umesh Yadav pushes it towards short covers.
Tossed up, full and on off, turning away, Umesh Yadav leans on to defend, but gets beaten on the outside edge. There is another huge shout for caught behind, but turned down.
Slower through the air, on off, Umesh Yadav prods forward and keeps it out to the off side.
Tossed up, full and on off, turning away, Axar Patel gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to block.
A bit short and on off, Axar Patel moves back and pushes it towards the bowler.
On middle, blocked out.
Short again and outside off, Axar Patel punches it towards sweeper covers for a single.
Another short delivery, on middle, Umesh Yadav pushes it towards mid off.
SIX! BOOM! Umesh Yadav makes his intent clear here! This is looped up, full and on middle, Umesh Yadav slog-sweeps it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Full and wide outside off, Axar Patel cuts this to backward point for a single.
SIX! In the air and it flies over the deep square leg fielder for a maximum. Fuller around pads, Umesh Yadav slog sweeps this for a maximum. Some crucial runs for India.
Fuller around middle, Umesh Yadav drills this back onto the stumps on the non-striking end.
On a length around middle, Umesh Yadav defends this out.
Tossed up around leg, Umesh Yadav goes for the big heave again but misses out and it deflects off his pads.
FOUR! A counter attack from the lower-order batter. Fuller around middle, Umesh Yadav clears his front leg and smashes this past the cow corner for a boundary. He is having fun out in the middle.
Off-break short in length, Axar Patel defends this off his back foot.
Flighted around middle, Axar Patel blocks this out.
Tossed up around middle, Axar Patel pushes this to long off for a single.
Short in length around off, Nathan Lyon pushes this sweeper cover for a single.
Quicker around middle, Axar Patel defends this in front.
Tossed up around middle, Axar Patel blocks this out with a front foot defensive stroke.
Short in length around middle, Umesh Yadav defends this off his front foot.

OUT! Five-wicket haul for Matthew Kuhnemann as he removes Umesh Yadav. On a length and on leg, Umesh Yadav looks to push this to off but gets beaten by the low bounce of this and the ball has hit his pads. Aussies appeal and the umpire had no doubt in raising his finger.
Tossed up and on off, Mohammed Siraj defends this.
Fuller and on off, Mohammed Siraj edges this wide of slip for no run.
Solid in defense has been Mohammed Siraj so far as he blocks this out too.
Length dragged back a bit, Mohammed Siraj defends this in front of silly point.
Flighted on leg, Axar Patel defends this off the front foot.

OUT! RUN OUT! Comical running costs the wicket of Siraj and India has been bowled out for 109 here. Fuller one around pads, Axar flicks this to square leg and runs the first hard and jogs back for the second but Siraj was not anticipating the second and was jogging around. a good throw from the deep towards the non-striking end sees Siraj short of his crease.
Short in length around off, Travis Head pushes this towards sweeper cover for a couple.
Tossed up around off, Travis Head defends this off the front foot.
Short in length around middle, Travis Head punches this off the back foot for a couple more this time to deep mid wicket.
Runs coming thick and fast. Fuller outside off, Travis Head punches this to sweeper cover for a single.
Carrom ball by Ashwin going down leg, Usman Khawaja looks to flick but deflects this off his hips.
On a length around pads, Usman Khawaja flicks this to fine leg for a single.
Fuller down leg, Usman Khawaja leaves this for the keeper.
Smart reflexes by Gill. Short in length around pads, Usman Khawaja deflects this of hips towards short leg.
Fuller around off, Usman Khawaja pushes this to dee mid-wicket for a single. Jadeja has overstepped too.
FOUR! Head is up and running with a boundary beside his name. Fuller around pads, Travis Head flicks this towards fine leg for a boundary. Aussies have started off well.

On a length around leg, Travis Head looks to defend but gets hit on the pads, Loud appeal from India but the umpire turns this down. Rohit asks for DRS and the TV replay shows the ball was going to hit the stumps after pitching in line. Head departs after scoring 9.
Short and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes this to short cover.
Quicker around off, Marnus Labuschagne keeps low to defend this out.
Full and wide outside off, Usman Khawaja drives this to cover for a single.
Grip and turn from Ashwin as he flights one around pads, Marnus Labuschagne flicks this off his pads towards fine leg for a single.
Fuller and much slower outside off, Usman Khawaja looks to defend but gets beaten.
Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja blocks this out.
Tossed up outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves this for the keeper.
Carrom ball coming in towards the pads, Usman Khawaja blocks this out.
Cleaned him up! Marginally short outside off, Marnus Labuschagne hops onto his back foot and looks to cut but gets an outside edge that chops back to the stumps. OH NO! Jadeja has overstepped.
Short and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne cuts this to backward point for a single.
NOT OUT! This is fuller around pads, Usman Khawaja flicks this to deep square leg for a couple. Umesh hits the bulls eye from the deep and the umpires have sent this upstairs, Khwaja is safely in.
Fuller around middle, Usman Khawaja defends this in front.
Fuller one darted in by Jadeja, Usman Khawaja blocks this out.
Fuller around middle, Usman Khawaja nudges this to short fine leg for single.
Fuller around middle, Marnus Labuschagne defends this solidly off his front foot.
Short in length around middle, Usman Khawaja nudges this to mid wicket for a couple.
Fuller outside off, Usman Khawaja blocks this out.
On a length around pads, Usman Khawaja edges this towards front of square.
Short in length and on off, Usman Khawaja defends this to cover for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Marnus Labuschagne defends this off the front foot.
Fuller around middle, Marnus Labuschagne dabs this off the surface to short leg. Gill does well to field this and keep it down to nothing.

Flighted around off, Cheteshwar Pujara uses his feet and tucks it straight to short mid-wicket.
Fires this one full and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara opens the face of his bat and guides it towards point.

Just short! This is floated on middle, turns away with some bounce, Virat Kohli looks to defend, but the extra bounce hits his thumb and loops up in the air. However, it falls just short of catching gully where Peter Handscomb dives forward, but fails to reach it.
Flatter, full and on leg, Virat Kohli nudges it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Good shot! Matthew Kuhnemann lands this short and outside off, Virat Kohli quickly moves on his back foot and cuts it wide of covers for a boundary.

OUT! LBW! Matthew Kuhnemann strikes! Virat Kohli looks disappointed, but he has to go back now to the hut. This is floated and lands around middle and leg, Virat Kohli thinks this is short enough and goes for the flick off the back foot, but the ball keep really low and goes under his bat to hit his pads. There is a huge appeal for LBW, and up goes the finger. Virat Kohli is not happy with his shot selection and does not even have a chat about taking the review. Australia are delighted to see the back of him.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja blocks it out.
Gives this one some air, on middle, Ravindra Jadeja keeps it out off his gloves onto the pitch.
Floated and on off, turning in sharply, Cheteshwar Pujara manages to work it with the inner half towards short fine leg.
Tossed up, full and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara leans on and blocks it out.
Flighted and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara advances down the track and tucks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Gives this one some air again, on middle, turning away, Ravindra Jadeja steers it towards point.
Shortish and on middle, angling in, Ravindra Jadeja moves back and nudges it towards square leg for a run.
Another short delivery and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara cuts it past cover-point as Travis Head chases it and slides in to keep it inside. Three runs taken!
FOUR! Fine shot! Matthew Kuhnemann lands this short and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara picks up the length early and smackes it wide of mid on for a boundary.
Floated, full and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara leans on to defends, but does so uppishly and wide of silly point.
Short again and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara cuts it through point for a single.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja chips it down to long on for a run.
FOUR! Cheteshwar Pujara is taking on Matthew Kuhnemann! This is flighted on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara skips down the track and drills it past the bowler and wide of mid on for another boundary.
Looped up, full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it on the front foot.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja defends it down the pitch.
Floated, full and on leg, Ravindra Jadeja keeps it out to the leg side.

TURN AND BOUNCE! This is flighted, full and on off, grips and turns away with bounce, Ravindra Jadeja misses and Alex Carey only manages to parry it behind him as Steven Smith from slips chases and mops it up. Two byes taken!
On off, kept out.
Tossed up and on off, turns away again, Ravindra Jadeja is beaten on the outside edge as he prods forward to defend. There is a stiffled appeal for caught behind, but turned down.
Darts this one full and on leg, Ravindra Jadeja flicks it though square leg for a single.
Short and outside off, turns away, Ravindra Jadeja is early into his punch, but the ball falls short of short covers this time.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja defends it on the front foot.
Floated, full and on off, Ravindra Jadeja is solid in his defense again.
Flighted, full and on off, Ravindra Jadeja keeps it out with the inner half to the leg side.
Flatter, full and on leg, Ravindra Jadeja turns it towards short leg region.
Short and around off, Ravindra Jadeja moves back and punches it towards sweeper covers for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off, Ravindra Jadeja blocks it towards silly point.
Floated, full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja knocks it down the pitch.
Flighted, full and on off, Ravindra Jadeja pushes it back to the bowler.
Slower through the air, on middle, Ravindra Jadeja leans on to defend, but gets an inside edge towards short fine leg.
Tossed up, full and on off, Ravindra Jadeja guides it wide of short third man where the fielder dives to his right to stop it. They cross.
Quicker, full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
Floated, short and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja stays back and keeps it out.
Tossed up, full and off, turns away with bounce again, Ravindra Jadeja is beaten on the front foot defense and Alex Carey gets hit on his chest while trying to collect it.
Flighted, full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja negotiates it well.
On off, kept out.
Flighted, full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja is solid in his defense again.
Short and outside off, Ravindra Jadeja cuts it past point for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off, Ravindra Jadeja pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter, short and on off, Ravindra Jadeja waits for it and cuts it close to the stumps towards point.
Floated, full and on leg, Ravindra Jadeja tucks it towards wide of mid on for a single.
A bit short and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara nudges it towards square leg for a run.
Slower through the air, on off, Ravindra Jadeja blocks it with soft hands, and gets an outiside edge on the bounce towards first slip.
Flighted, full and on off, Ravindra Jadeja defens it on the front foot.
Fuller around off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this in front.
Tossed up around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara walks down and tucks this to mid wicket for a single.
On a length going down with the arm, Ravindra Jadeja gets hit on the pads. Loud appeal but umpire turns this down.
On a length pitching outside leg and turning sharp up and over off. Carey gets some glove on this from behind the wicket.

OUT! LBW! Nathan Lyon strikes! This is on a length around middle and leg, Ravindra Jadeja strides forward to defend but gets hit on his pads. Aussies appeal loud and long for this but the umpire turns this down. Steven Smith was prompt in asking for a DRS, TV replay shows all three reds and Ravindra Jadeja has to walk back to the hut.
Tossed up around off, Shreyas Iyer defends this off the front foot.
Fuller around off, Cheteshwar Pujara pushes this to the off side for a single.
Tossed up around off, Shreyas Iyer strides out and defends this.
Tossed up outside off, Shreyas Iyer blocks this out to silly point.
Short in length around off, Shreyas Iyer defends this to short cover.
On a length around middle, Shreyas Iyer pushes this to short cover.
Tossed up around off, Shreyas Iyer defends this with a gentle push back to the bowler.  THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Good leave down the leg by Pujara. On a length going harmlessly away from stumps, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves this.
Fuller around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara tucks this to square leg for a single.
Turning and staying low. On a length around middle, turns sharp and hits Iyer on his pads.
On a length around middle, Shreyas Iyer defends this well.
Lyon drifts on around pads, Shreyas Iyer blocks this wide of forward short leg.
Slider an on middle, Shreyas Iyer defends this out.
Tossed up around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this out.
FOUR! Down the track comes Pujara and smashes this for a boundary. Fuller around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara dances down the track and glances this for a boundary towards the deep mid-wicket region.
Length dragged back a bit, Cheteshwar Pujara punches this off the back foot for a single towards sweeper cover.
SIX! Too short and this was begging to be hit. Short in length around middle, Shreyas Iyer picks up length quickly and pulls one over the mid-wicket fence for a maximum. India takes the lead now!
Fuller around pads, Shreyas Iyer pushes this to mid on.
Tossed up around middle, Shreyas Iyer defends this off the font foot.
Short in length around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara nudges this to square leg for a single.
Quicker one floated around middle, Shreyas Iyer defends this to short leg.
FOUR! Gloves this away for a boundary behind the wicket. Tossed up around pads, Shreyas Iyer looks to flick but gets a good glove on this as it travels past the keeper for a boundary.
FOUR! Luck favors India as this time an edge flies for a boundary. Fuller and outside off, Shreyas Iyer looks to push towards cover but gets a leading edge for a boundary towards the third man.
Length dragged back a bit, Iyer nudges this wide of Peter at short leg for a single.
Tossed up around off, Cheteshwar Pujara milks this to short mid wicket.
FOUR! Iyer has walked out with a positive mindset. Short in length around middle, Shreyas Iyer punched this off the back foot wide of mid on for a boundary.
Fuller outside off, Shreyas Iyer defends this to short third man.
Fuller around off, Shreyas Iyer blocks this out.
SIX! Iyer is on a move here. Slightly short in length, Iyer goes deep in his crease and pulls this over mid-wicket for a maximum.
Tossed up around off, Shreyas Iyer defends this in front.
Fuller around off, Shreyas Iyer blocks this out to silly point. Anther big over for India.
Fuller around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves this with a backward short leg lurking near him.
Fuller around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara tucks this wide of backward short leg.
Fuller around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara pushes this back to the bowler.
Tossed up around off, Cheteshwar Pujara taps this to short cover and runs a single.
Fuller around middle, Shreyas Iyer defends this to forward short leg.
Short in length around pads, Shreyas Iyer nudges this to the left of square leg for a single.
Starts off with a loose one. Full and wide outside leg, Alex Carey does well to stop this.

OUT! SPECTACULARLY TAKEN! What a catch this is by Usman Khawaja. Fuller around middle, Iyer glances this towards short mid-wicket, Usman Khwaja dives to his left and takes a stunner diving sideways. Umpires want to have a look at the catch and the replay shows this is a fair take. Inspired bowling change by Smith as Starc removes the dangerous-looking Iyer.
Howout: c Usman Khawaja b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Toe crusher by Mitchell Starc, Bharat dugs this out well.
On a length around pads, Srikar Bharat edges this from the inside towards fine leg for a single.
Fuller around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara nudges this to short mid wicket.
Fuller around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks this towards deep square leg for a single.
Fuller around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara nudges this to square leg for a single.
Tossed up around middle, Srikar Bharat looks to defend but gets a thickish inside edge just past forward short leg. Single taken.
Tossed up around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this back to the bowler.
Fuller around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks this to short fine leg.
Fuller and on pads, Cheteshwar Pujara clips this towards short fine leg.
Fuller around off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this keeping low.
Fuller drifting down leg, Srikar Bharat looks for the leg glance but gets it clipped off his pads. Carey dives full stretch to his left and saves a certain boundary.
Fuller delivery around off, Srikar Bharat drives this to mid off for no run.
Full and wide outside off, Srikar Bharat drives this straight to short cover.
Full and wide outside off, Srikar Bharat guides this to third man for a single.
On a length around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara nudges this to square leg for no run.
Full and wide drifting down leg, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to flick but misses out.

OUT! TIMBER! Nathan Lyon does what he does best! Srikar Bharat goes back to the hut for yet another low score. Lyon bowls this quicker and on middle, angling away, Srikar Bharat leans on and play for the turn, but this one straightens and beats his bat to go through and disturb the stumps. India in a bit of a trouble now as they lose their sixth wicket.
Floated, short and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin keeps it out on the back foot, but the ball spins a along the ground and he kicks it away.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin leans on and blocks it out.
Flatter, full and outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin slices it past point for a brace and gets off the mark.
This one keeps low, on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin moves back and tucks it towards short mid-wicket where the fielder fumbles a bit but no harm done.
Flighted, full and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin chips it towards long on for a run.
This is on a good length but down the leg side, Ravichandran Ashwin makes an easy leave.
Touch fuller but down the leg side again, Ravichandran Ashwin misses his flick. Starc is looking for reverse swing, but he is not able to get his line right.
FOUR! Nice shot! Mitchell Starc serves this full and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin leans on and drives it frimly through covers for a boundary.
On a length and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin clips it towards short mid-wicket.
Mitchell Starc nails the yorker this time, on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin digs it out well towards short mid-wicket.
A slower one now, on a length and down the leg side, Ravichandran Ashwin lets it go and Alex Carey only manages to parry it towards fine leg. A bye is taken.
Flatter, short and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin keeps it out towards point.
Short again and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it towards backward square leg for a single.
Tossed up, full and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to block it, but misses and the ball loops up off his pads as short leg catches it.
Floated, full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara uses his feet and turns it towards short mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter and around leg, Cheteshwar Pujara tickles it wide of short fine leg where Todd Murphy dives to his right to stop it. They cross. Murphy certainly saved three runs there.
Shortish agai and on leg, Ravichandran Ashwin clips it towards the right of short leg as the fielder gathers it moving to that side.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara leans on and keeps it to the leg side.
Floated, full and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it on the front foot.
Flighted, full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it towards short mid-wicket.
Looped up, full and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it towards short covers.
Slower through the air, on middle, turns away sharply, Cheteshwar Pujara tries to poke at it, but misess.
A maiden over! This is floated, full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara is solid in his defense again.
Tossed up, full and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin drives it towards mid off for a single.
Floated, full and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara nudges it wide of square leg for a run.
Pushed through quciker, on middle, turns in sharply, Ravichandran Ashwin looks to block it, but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball goes nowhere.
Short and around off, Ravichandran Ashwin cuts it wide of point where Travis Head dives to his right to stop it. They cross.
Short again and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara clips it uppishly but just past short leg for another run.
Flighted, full and on middl, Ravichandran Ashwin keeps it out to the off side.

FIFTY FOR PUJARA! This has been an excellent knock under pressure from him and he will look to continue like this in this match. He gets a standing ovation from the crowd as well. Coming to the delivery, this is a low full toss, on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara uses his feet and drills it towards long on for one.
Tossed up, full and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin blocks it out to the off side.
Floated, full and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin knocks it towards cover-point.
A bit short and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin pushes it towards short covers.
Flighted, full and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin looks defend, but gets an outside edge along the ground towards second slip.
Shortish and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin moves back but miscues his flick onto his pads as the ball goes nowhere.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend, but gets an inside edge onto his body.
Floated, full and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara leans on to block but misses and the ball loops up off his pads towards the leg slip region.
Flighted, full and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara keeps it out to the off side.
Flatter and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara uses his feet and turns it towards short mid-wicket.
Quicker, short and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it towards short mid-wicket.
Gives this one some air, on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it towards point.
Tossed up, full and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin guides it towards backward point.
Short and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin moves back and cuts it towards sweeper covers for a single.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara keeps it out to the leg side.

DROPPED! A tough chance, but Marnus Labuschagne should have done better. This is short and around off, turns away, Cheteshwar Pujara is early into his cut and plays it uppishly wide of short covers where Marnus Labuschagne dives to his left, gets both hands to it, but spills it out. A single is taken. This could turn out to be a huge moment in the game.

FOUR! Matthew Kuhnemann lands this short again and on leg, Ravichandran Ashwin gets a bit hurried by the bounce, and ends up chipping it. However, it has enough power to go over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Just short! A full toss, on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin whips it aerially which just falls short of Nathan Lyon at mid-wicket.

OUT! LBW! Nathan Lyon gets a five-for! A huge appeal for LBW, but turned down. Australia takes the review as Lyon is very confident about this. Nathan Lyon pushes this quicker through the air, on middle and leg, turning in, Ravichandran Ashwin prods forward to defend, but play down the wrong line and gets hit on his front pad. Howevere, the on-field decision is Not Out as it hard to see whether it is bat first or pad first. UltraEdgs shows that it is pad first and Ball Tracking indicates three reds. Ravichandran Ashwin looks down in disappointment, but he has to make that long walk back . India seven down now!
Tossed up, full and on middle, Axar Patel blocks it out.

Flighted, full and on off, turning away, Axar Patel prods forward to defend, but gets beaten on the outside edge as Alex Carey collects it. Steven Smith appeals for the caught behind, but turned down.
Flighted, full and on off, Axar Patel defends it to the off side.
Looped up, full and on off, Axar Patel drives it towards long off for a single and gets off the mark.
Flatter, full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it back towards the bowler.
Quicker, short and on off, Axar Patel pushes it towards short covers.
Flatter, short and on middle, Axar Patel keeps it down to the off side.
Tossed up, full and on off, Axar Patel drives it towards long off for a single.
Flighted and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara uses his feet and turns it towards short mid-wicket.
Shortish and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara moves back and knocks it back towards the bowler.
Fires this one full and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara misses his flick as Alex Carey deflects it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, Axar Patel blocks this out.
Flighted outside off, Axar Patel defends this off the front foot.
Slider outside off, Axar Patel looks to hop onto his back foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length around off, Axar Patel pushes this past diving short cover for a single.
Short in length around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara tucks this to square leg for a single.
Tossed up pitching outside leg, Axar Patel looks to block but gets hit on the pads. Gentle appeal by the Aussies but the umpire has turned this down.
Tossed up outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara strides forward and defends this well.
Flighted around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara pushes this back to the bowler.
Well dug out by Pujara. Fuller delivery keeping really low, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this of the tow end.
Fuller around off, Cheteshwar Pujara leans down and defends this.

Fuller around pads, Pujara looks to flick this to fine leg but misses out, Carey does well to collect this down to his left as he removes the bails in a flash. Umpire wants to check stumping and the TV replay shows he is safely behind the crease.
Fuller delivery around leg, Safely negotiated by Pujara to end the over.
Fuller delivery wide of off, Axar Patel drives this to long off for a single.
Fuller around off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this well.
Fuller delivery around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks this out.
Fuller delivery outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this well wide of short leg.
Fuller delivery around pads Cheteshwar Pujara nudges this to short fine leg.
Short in length around leg, Cheteshwar Pujara works this fine to short fine leg.
Tossed up wide outside off, Axar Patel leaves this for the keeper.
On a length around off, Axar Patel defends this off the front foot.
Fuller one around off, Axar Patel defends this past second slip.
Fuller one on off, Axar Patel drives this just short of short cover.
Length dragged back outside off, Axar Patel looks to cut but fails to connect. Lucky that the ball was not in line of stumps.
Fuller delivery around pads, Axar Patel defends this off the front foot.
Full and wide outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this on the on side.
Fuller one around off, Cheteshwar Pujara clips this to fine leg.
SIX! Massive hit by Pujara. Tossed up around off, Cheteshwar Pujara jogs out and smashes this over the deep mid-wicket fence for a maximum.
Length dragged back a bit and Pujara defends this back to the bowler.
Fuller around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara pushes this to short mid wicket.
On a lengt around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara works this fine to short fine leg.
Fuller outside off, Axar Patel drills this past the bowler for a single.
Fuller delivery around pads, Cheteshwar Pujara nudges this wide of short mid wicket for a single.
Toosed up outside off, Axar Patel looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short and wide outside off, Axar Patel slaps this off the back foot towards sweeper cover for a couple.
Shortin length angling in, Axar Patel defends this well off his back foot.
Yorker by Murphy and Axar keeps this out.
Short in length around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends this off the front foot.
Tossed up on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks this out.

OUT! TAKEN! Flash of brilliance from the Australian skipper. Fuller around pads, Pujara looks to flick and gets a faint edge to his leg. Steven Smith gets really low down to his right and grabs a one-handed stunner. It needed something spectacular to dismiss Puajara and Smith has come out with one.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Fuller and turning in towards the pads, Umesh Yadav looks to defend but gets beaten on the inside as the ball hits his pads. Loud appeal by the Aussies and the umpire gives it out. Umesh Yadav asks for a review and the replay shows the ball was missing stumps.

OUT! Taken in the deep. Fuller around middle, Umesh slogs hard at this but fails to clear the fence as he lands one in the hands of Green at the deep mid-wicket fence. Trouble adds up for the hosts here.
Howout: c Cameron Green b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Tossed up, full and on middle, Mohammed Siraj defends it with the inner half past leg slip. They do no take the single.

Mitchell Starc tries for the yorker, but serves this down the leg, Axar Patel misses his flick as his bat hits the ground, and the ball goes through to Alex Carey behind the stumps. There is a quiet enquiry by Starc, but turned down. However, Steven Smith takes the reveiw, but UltraEdge clearly shows that there is no bat involved and Australia lose their review.
Back of a length and on middle, Axar Patel defends it back to the bowler.
Mitchell Starc nails another brilliant yorker, on middle, swinging in, Axar Patel does well to dig it out towards short mid-wicket.
Overpitched and on middle, Axar Patel drills it towards long on. He refuse the run.
This is pitched up and outside off, Axar Patel squeezes it towards point for a single.
Fuller and on off, Mohammed Siraj keeps it out with the outer half as the ball rolls towards the right of the keeper.
Tossed up, full and on off, Axar Patel pushes it towards sweeper covers and denies the single.
Floated, full and on leg, Axar Patel clips it towards deep mid-wicket.
SIX! BANG! Axar Patel goes big now! This is fligthed, full and on middle, Axar Patel goes down and slog-sweeps it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Short and outside off, Axar Patel cuts it towards sweeper covers for a single.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Mohammed Siraj leans on and blocks it out.
Floated, full and on middle, Mohammed Siraj keeps it out towards short leg.
Fuller outside off, Axar Patel drives this picture perfect to the fielder at long off. Single not taken.
On a length outside off, Axar Patel looks to poke but gets beaten.
Fuller one down leg, Axar Patel missed out on a flick here.
Full and wide outside off, Axar Patel lets this go to the keeper.
Full toss on pads, Axar Patel looks to flick but misses out completely.
Yorker nailed in perfectly. Axar manages to keep this out.
Tossed up around pads, Mohammed Siraj deflects this off his pads to short leg.
Fuller delivery around middle, Mohammed Siraj defends this well.

OUT! TIMBER! Nathan Lyon gets the last wicket! Mohammed Siraj tries to be aggressive, but loses his wicket in the process. Lyon flights this up, on middle, Mohammed Siraj skips down the track and goes for the big slog, but gets beaten in the flight and plays all over it as the ball goes through to rattle the stumps. India have been bowled out for 163 runs here. The target for Australia will be 76 runs! THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Tossed up outside off, Usman Khawaja looks to defend but gets beaten. Great start to the day.

OUT! OH DEAR! Is this the start of something special for India. Ashwin gives this a bit more air and Usman Khawaja looks to defend but gets a faint edge of the outside of his bat and Srikar Bharat collects this with ease. First one down for the Aussies in no time. Khwaja reviews this decision and there is a clear spike as the ball passes his bat. Australia loses Khwaja and a review.
Howout: c Srikar Bharat b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: Fuller and quicker around pads, Marnus Labuschagne defends this to short leg.
Tossed up near the pads, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this out just in front of short leg.
Fuller around middle, Marnus Labuschagne defends this in front.
Flatter and quicker around off, Marnus Labuschagne defends this off his back foot. A successful over comes to an end for the hosts.
Tossed up around pads, Travis Head pushes this to deep mid wicket for a single.
Fuller around pads, Marnus Labuschagne nudges this to short fine leg.
FOUR! Sigh of relief for the Aussies. Short and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne hops back and cuts this through the gap at cover-point for a boundary.
